      "description": "Available is a 2011 BMW M3 (E92) featuring the iconic S65 4.0-liter naturally aspirated V8. This high-revving power unit utilizes eight individual throttle bodies and a 12.0:1 compression ratio to deliver a linear power band peaking at 8,400 RPM. The chassis remains taut, equipped with Electronic Damper Control (EDC) and a variable M differential lock for superior lateral grip. Recent service includes a comprehensive throttle actuator overhaul and rod bearing inspection, ensuring the longevity of the valvetrain and crank journals. While showing minor signs of road use consistent with its history, the car maintains excellent mechanical integrity and structural rigidity. A purist\u2019s spec with a 6-speed manual gearbox, this M3 offers an analog driving experience increasingly rare in the modern era.",
